        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 28 at 11:39AM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 1138 AM EDT/1038 AM CDT/, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of
strong thunderstorms near Town of Pines, or near Trail Creek, moving
east at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Byron, Union Pier, Hudson Lake, Grand Beach, Waterford, Michiana
Shores, Trail Creek, Otis, Pottawattomie Park, Rolling Prarie,
Michiana, Lakeside In Berrien County, Pinola, Hesston, Michigan City,
La Porte, Long Beach, Springville, Pottawattamie Park, and New
Buffalo.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 80 in Indiana between mile markers 38 and 61.
Interstate 94 in Indiana between mile markers 33 and 45.
Interstate 94 in Michigan between mile markers 0 and 9.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
